# Localization Testing Framework

## 📖 Overview

This document outlines my localization testing methodology, best practices, and cultural considerations for QA across multiple languages and regions.

---

## 🌐 Localization QA Scope

### What I Test in Localization

- ✅ **Text Rendering:** Character display, fonts, special characters
- ✅ **Text Overflow/Truncation:** Content fitting in UI elements
- ✅ **Translation Accuracy:** Meaning and context preservation
- ✅ **Cultural Appropriateness:** Local customs, colors, symbolism
- ✅ **Date/Time/Number Formatting:** Region-specific formats
- ✅ **Keyboard Layouts:** Language-specific input methods
- ✅ **Audio Localization:** Voice-overs, dubbing, sound effects
- ✅ **RTL (Right-to-Left) Languages:** Arabic, Hebrew compatibility
- ✅ **Terminology Consistency:** Consistent terminology throughout product

---

## 🧪 Localization Testing Checklist

### Pre-Testing
- [ ] Verify all translation files are loaded correctly
- [ ] Confirm language selection mechanism works
- [ ] Test locale/region settings are properly applied
- [ ] Check font support for target languages

### UI/Text Testing
- [ ] All UI text displays in target language
- [ ] Text fits properly in all UI elements (no overflow)
- [ ] No hardcoded text remains in interface
- [ ] Special characters and accents display correctly
- [ ] Formatting (bold, italics, colors) works correctly
- [ ] Links and clickable text function properly
- [ ] Buttons have appropriate label sizes

### Content Testing
- [ ] Dialogue is appropriate and culturally sensitive
- [ ] Names, places, cultural references are localized appropriately
- [ ] Units of measurement are converted (miles vs. kilometers, etc.)
- [ ] Currency symbols and amounts display correctly
- [ ] Date and time formats follow regional conventions

### Technical Testing
- [ ] Keyboard input works for language-specific characters
- [ ] Copy/paste functionality preserves special characters
- [ ] Search functionality works with localized terms
- [ ] Encoding is correct (UTF-8 compatibility)
- [ ] Text direction (LTR/RTL) is correct

### Gameplay/Functionality Testing
- [ ] All features work identically in all languages
- [ ] No crashes or errors due to localization
- [ ] Performance is not impacted by localized content
- [ ] Audio syncs properly with localized subtitles

